=Hello,
Here is the current Google Drive Permissions Audit for {{ $now.format('yyyy-MM-dd') }}.

See the full report here - [Audit Gsheet]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}{{ $('Create New Sheet').first().json.spreadsheetId}}/edit?gid={{ $('Create New Sheet').first().json.sheetId}})

## Shared with Anyone (Public Link)
{{
$input.all().map(item => item.json)
  .filter(row => row.type === 'anyone')
  .map(row => `* ${row.file_name} ([link]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}{row.file_id}/edit?usp=sharing))`)
  .join('\n')
}}

## Shared with External Users (By Invite)
{{
$input.all().map(item => item.json)
  .filter(row => row.type == 'user')
  .map(row => `* ${row.file_name} ([link]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}{row.file_id}/edit?usp=sharing))`)
  .join('\n')
}}

Please review if permissions for these documents need to be updated.

Best regards,
N8N Gdrive Permissions Audit Workflow

parameters.content:
## 1. Scheduled Trigger to Audit Everyday
[Read more about the Scheduled Trigger node]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

The Scheduled Trigger is used to automate this workflow at a frequency which meets your data access auditing requirements. Here we've set it to run everyday and for each run a new Google Sheet is created to capture the results of the audit.

Check out the example Sheet here: {{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}
